\begin_inset Formula \[
\frac{6-y}{8}=RLRry=rgr\; g\; rgr\; ry=\left(rg\right)^{3}y\]

\end_inset

The bits to the left are all zero, and so one has 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\frac{6-y}{2^{n+3}}=L^{n}RLRry=g^{n}\left(rg\right)^{3}y\]

\end_inset

For readability, the subscript 
\begin_inset Formula $D$
\end_inset

 was dropped above two equations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Consider then the action of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{L}_{c}$
\end_inset

 on 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{l}\left(x\right)=f\left(\left(2l+1\right)x\right)$
