 & \qquad\cdots+\frac{1}{2^{n}}f\, L^{n-3}RLLr\,3\left(x-\frac{1}{3}\right)+\cdots\end{align*}

\end_inset

So, for example, if 
\begin_inset Formula $f=t_{w,l}$
\end_inset

 the Takagi function defined in the previous section, one then has, for
 
\begin_inset Formula $k\ge3$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $l=1$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $0\le x<1/3$
\end_inset

, that
\end_layout

